commit_msg:
Fix C# Generation for UDT Tuple Field (#270)

Fixed an issue with the C# generation for UDT classes where tuple fields of the UDT where not being correctly parsed. Added some tests for this situation.
annotator_comment: When defining a UDT (user defined type) with a named item whose type is a non-singleton tuple, the C# code generation step produces invalid properties that then fail to compile when running dotnet build.
